## Implementation Plan: --fields flag (#347)

### Problem
All `--json` commands dump the full data object. Agents pay per token and lose reasoning capacity with every irrelevant field.

### Solution
Add `--fields` flag to all 14 commands with `--json` output.

### Design
- `filterFields(data, fields)` — dot-notation traversal, handles arrays, nested objects, primitives passthrough
- `parseFieldsList(input)` — comma-separated parsing with trim/dedup
- `writeJson(stream, data, fields?)` — optional filtering before serialization
- `FIELDS_FLAG` — shared Stricli flag definition in list-command.ts

### Commands updated (14)
auth/whoami, event/view, issue/explain, issue/list, issue/plan, issue/view,
log/list, log/view, org/list, project/create, project/list, project/view,
trace/list, trace/view

### Special cases
- issue/list: threaded through OrgAllIssuesOptions / ResolvedTargetsOptions
- issue/plan: threaded through OutputSolutionOptions
- log/list: refactored to options objects (avoid 5-param lint)
- project/list: each handler computes parsedFields independently

### Known limitation
Dot-notation is ambiguous for keys containing literal dots (e.g. `{"a":{".":false}}`).
This is documented in AGENTS.md and property tests use restricted key charset.

### Testing
- Property-based: 7 tests in json.property.test.ts (identity, subset, array length, dot-notation, no extra keys, parseFieldsList properties)
- Unit: 20+ tests in json.test.ts (top-level, nesting, missing fields, null/undefined/primitives, arrays, writeJson integration)
- 48 new tests, 885 new expect() calls
